The paper discusses techniques for efficient inference in relational probability models, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of knowledge compilation techniques and the comparison of different target circuits suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and database systems (cs.DB). The use of low-level programs as a target circuit suggests a focus on programming languages (cs.PL) and software engineering (cs.SE).
